defaultMark defaultSimmondsdefault:default It is something that we are prepared to consider. You are right that the waters around Pitcairn are pristine. We need to find mechanisms to stimulate—or to get off the ground—the Pitcairn economy, and eco-tourism is a possibility.  That might revolve around a marine protected area, but there are challenges that relate to enforcement, particularly bearing in mind the isolated location of Pitcairn and the size of the marine protected area that we would be talking about.
